Rating: 4
This was a fabulous hit for Christmas dinner. I used all shiitake. If you're lucky enough to live near a large Asian populaiton you can pick them up for around $2.50 per pound at a good Chinese supermarket -otherwise it would have been much more costly. I used fresh herbs and Parmigiano Reggiano instead of gruyere. I put cheese on each layer and made the entire gratin (with the exception of browning the cheese on top) the day before to save oven space. An hour before dinner I put it in the oven covered at 325 for about 25 minutes then I sprinkled the cheese on top and browned it. We had leftovers panfried the next day with leftover tenderloin. It looks so difficult and elegant but it's actually a breeze to make. I'll make this every year.

