Rating: 4
This recipe turned out excellent. I used 1 lb. each of shitake, portabello, and button mushrooms. I used 1 tbsp. fresh thyme and rosemary instead of dried. I reduced the garlic from 3 tbsp. to 1 tbsp because I skipped the chicken broth step. Instead I used about 1/4 cup white wine and cooked until wine evaporated. Remove from heat. Follow the rest of the recipe. Made it 6 hours in advance and reheat in oven at 350 for about 30 minutes. Great dish and will definitely make it again! Everyone enjoyed this dish a lot!

